1
00:00:14,633 --> 00:00:16,400
I think I came at
the wrong time.

2
00:00:16,467 --> 00:00:17,733
I might be interrupting you.

3
00:00:18,200 --> 00:00:19,567
He's my boyfriend.

4
00:00:19,633 --> 00:00:21,967
The one I told you
I was looking for.

5
00:00:22,400 --> 00:00:25,500
I helped you out because I don't
want the situation to worsen.

6
00:00:25,567 --> 00:00:27,833
I still remember what
you did to my son.

7
00:00:28,500 --> 00:00:30,400
Go ahead! Sue me!

8
00:00:30,467 --> 00:00:35,167
I will do everything to
file a case against you.

9
00:00:35,267 --> 00:00:36,600
Hang on! Let me explain!

10
00:00:37,167 --> 00:00:38,100
Yen!

11
00:00:38,167 --> 00:00:39,433
I get that your girlfriend
kissed you

12
00:00:39,500 --> 00:00:42,033
- because she missed you!
- She's not my girlfriend!

13
00:00:42,100 --> 00:00:43,900
So what do you call that?
A fling?

14
00:00:43,967 --> 00:00:46,133
I don't want our family
to get ruined again.

15
00:00:46,200 --> 00:00:49,933
And I don't want my name
and reputation

16
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:54,900
in the banking community ruined
because of your foolishness.

17
00:00:54,967 --> 00:00:56,633
Why did you tell Yenyen
I'm your boyfriend?

18
00:00:56,700 --> 00:00:58,633
Did you get amnesia
from the plane crash?

19
00:00:58,700 --> 00:01:00,533
We broke up before
we left Davao!

20
00:01:00,600 --> 00:01:03,767
I will do everything, anything,
just to win you back again.

21
00:01:03,833 --> 00:01:06,133
Just to make you mine.
Please, don't leave me.

22
00:01:06,200 --> 00:01:07,133
Not this time.

23
00:01:07,633 --> 00:01:09,467
So I'm asking you,

24
00:01:09,533 --> 00:01:12,633
just please stay away
from my boyfriend.

25
00:01:12,700 --> 00:01:15,733
Because I just can't
afford to lose him again.

26
00:01:15,800 --> 00:01:17,267
Stay away from me, Red.

27
00:01:32,567 --> 00:01:33,400
Why are you acting that way?

28
00:01:36,700 --> 00:01:37,900
Why does it seem like
you're forgetting

29
00:01:37,967 --> 00:01:39,533
everything that happened
on the island?

30
00:01:41,033 --> 00:01:42,567
We have plans, don't we?

31
00:01:44,067 --> 00:01:45,967
You'll introduce me
to your mom...

32
00:01:47,333 --> 00:01:49,567
and I'll introduce you
to my parents.

33
00:01:52,533 --> 00:01:55,733
Why does it seem like you're
throwing everything away?

34
00:01:56,333 --> 00:01:59,533
Red, do you think it's
that easy for me?

35
00:02:01,033 --> 00:02:02,667
It's so hard.

36
00:02:04,767 --> 00:02:07,533
It's hard because everything
I showed you...

37
00:02:08,133 --> 00:02:11,467
everything I made you
feel is real.

38
00:02:13,200 --> 00:02:15,600
Yes, we made plans.

39
00:02:15,967 --> 00:02:18,867
But I didn't know
there was Sabina.

40
00:02:19,433 --> 00:02:20,800
Yen, I don't understand!

41
00:02:20,867 --> 00:02:24,167
What I don't understand is
your situation with Sabina!

42
00:02:24,233 --> 00:02:26,233
I want to stay out of it, Red!

43
00:02:27,667 --> 00:02:30,167
- Leave me out of it.
- Yen, please.

44
00:02:30,233 --> 00:02:34,000
I will do everything, please.
Don't leave me, Yen.

45
00:02:35,100 --> 00:02:38,033
- No, Red. We're over.
- Did you already forget

46
00:02:38,100 --> 00:02:40,167
everything we've been through?

47
00:02:41,967 --> 00:02:43,300
Red, we're over.

48
00:02:43,367 --> 00:02:44,500
Yen, please, no.

49
00:02:45,600 --> 00:02:46,833
Are you throwing
everything away?

50
00:02:47,300 --> 00:02:48,900
Is everything that easy for you?

51
00:02:50,933 --> 00:02:52,233
No, Red.

52
00:02:52,300 --> 00:02:52,867
No.

53
00:02:52,933 --> 00:02:54,200
It seems like you're

54
00:02:54,267 --> 00:02:55,400
- throwing everything away.
- No, no.

55
00:02:56,800 --> 00:03:01,500
Red, maybe we needed each
other to survive.

56
00:03:03,567 --> 00:03:04,667
I admit...

57
00:03:06,167 --> 00:03:09,100
I was happy with you
on the island.

58
00:03:11,700 --> 00:03:14,367
I feel safer when
you're beside me.

59
00:03:15,233 --> 00:03:16,033
But Red...

60
00:03:16,600 --> 00:03:18,633
Red, maybe that's the
farthest we can go.

61
00:03:20,333 --> 00:03:21,267
I'm sorry.

62
00:03:23,767 --> 00:03:25,033
I'm sorry.

63
00:03:26,833 --> 00:03:28,367
You're so unfair!

64
00:03:28,433 --> 00:03:29,767
You're being so unfair!

65
00:03:31,233 --> 00:03:32,200
Don't do this.

66
00:03:34,933 --> 00:03:35,733
Don't do this.

67
00:03:39,700 --> 00:03:40,867
- Don't do this.
- I'm sorry.

68
00:03:41,767 --> 00:03:43,833
- I'm sorry.
- Yen, don't leave me.

69
00:03:43,900 --> 00:03:44,967
Yen, please.

70
00:03:45,033 --> 00:03:45,733
Please.

71
00:03:46,100 --> 00:03:49,167
We have so many plans.

72
00:03:50,233 --> 00:03:53,100
- Red, I'm sorry.
- We have so many plans, Yen.

73
00:03:53,167 --> 00:03:54,467
I'm sorry.

74
00:03:54,567 --> 00:03:55,333
I'm sorry.
Don't...

75
00:03:58,300 --> 00:03:59,033
Don't...

76
00:04:00,800 --> 00:04:01,933
Yen, no, please.

77
00:04:02,800 --> 00:04:03,667
I'm sorry.

78
00:04:04,067 --> 00:04:04,767
I'm sorry.

79
00:04:09,600 --> 00:04:10,467
Yen, please!

80
00:04:13,867 --> 00:04:15,133
Yen, please!

81
00:04:18,067 --> 00:04:19,233
Yen, please!

82
00:04:20,667 --> 00:04:21,333
Yen!

83
00:04:26,633 --> 00:04:28,800
Yen, don't do this to me!

84
00:04:49,100 --> 00:04:50,000
You know what, Eden?

85
00:04:51,367 --> 00:04:53,500
I won't ask if you're okay.

86
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:56,100
Because it's clear
that you're not.

87
00:05:01,700 --> 00:05:04,233
I did the right thing, didn't I?

88
00:05:06,733 --> 00:05:08,233
But why...

89
00:05:10,000 --> 00:05:12,500
why does it feel so heavy?

90
00:05:17,133 --> 00:05:19,333
Why am I the one hurting?

91
00:05:24,233 --> 00:05:25,233
You know Eden...

92
00:05:26,933 --> 00:05:28,767
even if you don't admit it,

93
00:05:31,500 --> 00:05:36,800
what you and Red had wasn't
just an island fling.

94
00:05:39,667 --> 00:05:40,867
You know why?

95
00:05:43,533 --> 00:05:44,167
Because...

96
00:05:45,400 --> 00:05:46,500
you love him.

97
00:05:48,100 --> 00:05:50,667
You're hurting because you're
already in love with him.

98
00:06:01,400 --> 00:06:05,233
I'd choose to get hurt...

99
00:06:08,400 --> 00:06:10,467
than be someone who
inflicts pain on others.

100
00:06:12,567 --> 00:06:14,100
I can't do that.

101
00:06:16,767 --> 00:06:17,667
You know what, Eden?

102
00:06:20,433 --> 00:06:22,400
We're on an island.

103
00:06:23,067 --> 00:06:27,667
And we're in the
midst of uncertainty.

104
00:06:28,767 --> 00:06:32,700
But you still put others
first before yourself.

105
00:06:35,867 --> 00:06:37,600
You think about others' welfare.

106
00:06:38,433 --> 00:06:40,667
At least you're not selfish.

107
00:06:42,467 --> 00:06:45,267
You're not selfish,
but you're a martyr.

108
00:06:46,700 --> 00:06:52,167
Just think of Red as
a lovely souvenir.

109
00:06:55,100 --> 00:06:56,867
A beautiful memory...

110
00:06:58,467 --> 00:07:03,367
and lesson you can bring
when you return to Manila.

111
00:07:06,333 --> 00:07:07,300
The only thing is,

112
00:07:07,933 --> 00:07:13,033
you can't hang him on your
bag or stick him on your fridge,

113
00:07:14,500 --> 00:07:18,433
but he will stay in your heart.

114
00:07:20,100 --> 00:07:21,167
You know...

115
00:07:23,067 --> 00:07:24,967
if it's only up to me,

116
00:07:26,933 --> 00:07:29,067
I want to erase everything,
Raichu.

117
00:07:30,300 --> 00:07:32,100
I want to reset.

118
00:07:35,700 --> 00:07:38,800
I got lost when I was
on the other island.

119
00:07:41,533 --> 00:07:44,300
I want to find my old self.

120
00:07:45,200 --> 00:07:48,133
I want to bring back
my direction.

121
00:07:49,833 --> 00:07:53,433
And that is to reunite
with my mother.

122
00:07:55,000 --> 00:07:57,467
I will do everything
to survive.

123
00:07:58,467 --> 00:08:00,233
To get out of this island.

124
00:08:04,367 --> 00:08:07,233
I want to be with my mom again.

125
00:08:26,900 --> 00:08:27,967
Red, you can sleep here.

126
00:08:28,033 --> 00:08:29,600
Let's sleep together,
just like before.

127
00:08:31,800 --> 00:08:33,433
Sab, don't you really get it?

128
00:08:34,133 --> 00:08:36,967
Why are you pushing
yourself to me?

129
00:08:37,667 --> 00:08:39,500
You know my answer to that, Red.

130
00:08:39,900 --> 00:08:44,067
Besides, don't you appreciate
the things I do for you?

131
00:08:44,567 --> 00:08:46,467
I know I have a lot
of shortcomings

132
00:08:46,533 --> 00:08:48,933
in our relationship, but please,

133
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:51,300
just give our relationship
a second chance.

134
00:08:51,367 --> 00:08:52,333
Please?

135
00:08:54,300 --> 00:08:56,933
Please, sleep here.

136
00:09:01,533 --> 00:09:02,233
Eden!

137
00:09:04,133 --> 00:09:05,867
Our bed is all set.
Come on!

138
00:09:06,700 --> 00:09:07,967
Okay, let's go to bed.

139
00:09:08,033 --> 00:09:09,833
Okay, Sab. I'll do
what you want.

140
00:09:12,300 --> 00:09:13,333
Are you jealous?

141
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:18,633
No.

142
00:09:21,200 --> 00:09:21,767
Okay.

143
00:09:23,600 --> 00:09:24,633
I'll give you what you want.

144
00:09:27,033 --> 00:09:29,100
I hope you won't regret
your decision.

145
00:09:37,067 --> 00:09:37,533
Ready?

146
00:09:38,600 --> 00:09:39,400
Let's sleep.

147
00:09:44,933 --> 00:09:45,933
Let's go, Eden.

148
00:10:04,533 --> 00:10:05,233
Raichu.

149
00:10:06,933 --> 00:10:07,533
Raichu.

150
00:10:09,233 --> 00:10:10,867
Come on, let's swim.

151
00:10:10,933 --> 00:10:11,633
What?

152
00:10:12,367 --> 00:10:15,633
Let's go find some food too.

153
00:10:15,700 --> 00:10:16,400
How?

154
00:10:17,300 --> 00:10:18,533
We'll use a spear.
Come on.

155
00:10:18,600 --> 00:10:19,367
I'll handle it.

156
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:21,333
I'll just get the spear.

157
00:10:21,400 --> 00:10:22,233
Hold on.

158
00:10:23,233 --> 00:10:24,067
Ouch.

159
00:10:33,833 --> 00:10:34,267
Hey!

160
00:10:35,067 --> 00:10:36,467
You're spearing your heart.
Come on.

161
00:10:36,533 --> 00:10:37,367
I thought we would go
spearfishing.

162
00:10:38,367 --> 00:10:39,333
It's too early for that.

163
00:10:42,167 --> 00:10:44,167
And you asked me to bring this.

164
00:11:06,200 --> 00:11:08,833
We can file a case
against Mrs. Ramos.

165
00:11:09,367 --> 00:11:11,600
If she has the intent
to kill you,

166
00:11:12,067 --> 00:11:13,900
that's frustrated homicide.

167
00:11:13,967 --> 00:11:16,067
And I'll be honest with you.

168
00:11:16,133 --> 00:11:17,967
It is not going to be easy.

169
00:11:18,500 --> 00:11:20,500
Are you financially
ready for this?

170
00:11:21,767 --> 00:11:23,333
Do we have to pay for it?

171
00:11:24,167 --> 00:11:29,167
I thought it was free,
like my sister's case before.

172
00:11:29,233 --> 00:11:31,167
We had a free lawyer.

173
00:11:31,767 --> 00:11:33,300
This is a private law firm.

174
00:11:34,267 --> 00:11:38,167
If you want a free lawyer,
you should go to PAO.

175
00:11:39,033 --> 00:11:43,167
But they only accept
defense cases.

176
00:11:43,267 --> 00:11:44,033
And with your case,

177
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:47,200
I don't think PAO
will accept it.

178
00:11:47,267 --> 00:11:48,800
Because you're the
one filing a lawsuit.

179
00:12:09,467 --> 00:12:10,500
Good morning.

180
00:12:11,967 --> 00:12:14,833
It feels good to
wake up with you.

181
00:12:17,933 --> 00:12:19,667
What are you doing?

182
00:12:21,167 --> 00:12:22,333
Red!

183
00:12:22,400 --> 00:12:23,333
Sabina!

184
00:12:23,400 --> 00:12:24,533
You're now awake.

185
00:12:24,600 --> 00:12:26,367
We borrowed your spear.

186
00:12:26,433 --> 00:12:27,800
We're going to fish.

187
00:12:27,867 --> 00:12:28,733
Okay.
Thank you.

188
00:12:31,167 --> 00:12:32,233
Come on. Let's go there.

189
00:12:50,333 --> 00:12:51,300
You want to help me?

190
00:12:51,600 --> 00:12:52,967
- Yeah.
- Here. Go ahead.

191
00:12:54,767 --> 00:12:55,867
Help me.

192
00:12:55,933 --> 00:12:56,700
Take it off.

193
00:14:02,667 --> 00:14:03,433
Come on.

194
00:14:03,500 --> 00:14:04,867
Let's catch some fish.

195
00:14:13,367 --> 00:14:13,733
Hey!

196
00:14:14,333 --> 00:14:16,767
So fabulous, Eden!

197
00:14:16,833 --> 00:14:17,933
Candidate number two

198
00:14:18,000 --> 00:14:20,967
is so ready for the
swimming competition.

199
00:14:21,033 --> 00:14:21,900
Judge!

200
00:14:22,533 --> 00:14:25,033
What can you say
about her performance?

201
00:14:25,967 --> 00:14:27,367
Our judge is half-naked too.

202
00:14:27,433 --> 00:14:28,367
Come on, let's go.

203
00:14:28,467 --> 00:14:29,367
Wait a sec.

204
00:14:33,700 --> 00:14:35,100
- There it is!
- Hurry up!

205
00:14:35,167 --> 00:14:37,300
- Here it is! Do it!
- Hang on.

206
00:14:37,367 --> 00:14:38,600
Hurry up!

207
00:14:38,667 --> 00:14:39,667
1, 2, 3...

208
00:14:39,733 --> 00:14:40,200
go!

209
00:14:45,500 --> 00:14:46,533
You're so good, Eden!

210
00:14:46,600 --> 00:14:48,367
You're so perfect!

211
00:14:56,533 --> 00:14:57,833
Are you sure about that?

212
00:14:58,933 --> 00:15:01,300
That woman really
has the nerve.

213
00:15:02,767 --> 00:15:05,800
Anyway, thank you very much
for that information.

214
00:15:05,867 --> 00:15:06,467
Thanks.
Bye.

215
00:15:09,733 --> 00:15:10,367
Who was that?

216
00:15:13,000 --> 00:15:14,000
Attorney Garcia.

217
00:15:15,933 --> 00:15:16,967
Can you believe it?

218
00:15:17,033 --> 00:15:21,300
Amanda went to his office...

219
00:15:22,300 --> 00:15:25,567
to tell him she would file
a case against me.

220
00:15:25,933 --> 00:15:27,200
She's going to sue me.

221
00:15:27,267 --> 00:15:29,967
The nerve of that woman.
How is she going to sue me?

222
00:15:30,700 --> 00:15:32,000
She doesn't have money.

223
00:15:40,333 --> 00:15:41,300
Good luck.

224
00:15:48,033 --> 00:15:49,933
It's so unfair.

225
00:15:50,900 --> 00:15:52,567
When you have the money,

226
00:15:52,633 --> 00:15:56,833
you can send someone
innocent to jail.

227
00:15:57,800 --> 00:15:59,133
While poor people like us

228
00:15:59,200 --> 00:16:02,933
can't even sue someone
who did us wrong.

229
00:16:04,100 --> 00:16:05,933
When will our justice system

230
00:16:06,000 --> 00:16:07,433
- improve?
- It's so hard.

231
00:16:08,167 --> 00:16:10,600
It's so hard to be poor, Dindi.

232
00:16:11,367 --> 00:16:16,167
We can fight against
rich people like Rina.

233
00:16:16,833 --> 00:16:18,100
She's right.

234
00:16:19,433 --> 00:16:27,000
The case might get dismissed
because I have no money.

235
00:16:28,333 --> 00:16:29,200
It hurts.

236
00:16:29,700 --> 00:16:31,433
But that's the truth.

237
00:16:32,967 --> 00:16:36,400
Maybe I should focus
on finding my daughter.

238
00:16:37,433 --> 00:16:39,267
What do we do now?

239
00:16:39,967 --> 00:16:40,800
Nothing.

240
00:16:42,500 --> 00:16:48,033
Maybe this is a sign that
I should just avoid Rina.

241
00:16:48,100 --> 00:16:49,133
To avoid trouble.

242
00:16:50,767 --> 00:16:51,733
You know if...

243
00:16:53,933 --> 00:16:57,067
if not for Eden, I
might have given up.

244
00:16:58,600 --> 00:17:03,733
My child is the only reason
I keep on moving forward.

245
00:17:06,400 --> 00:17:08,667
I'll just use my time
to find my daughter.

246
00:17:08,733 --> 00:17:11,100
Because if I lose her,

247
00:17:11,167 --> 00:17:14,700
our efforts to get me
out of prison

248
00:17:14,800 --> 00:17:16,033
and reunite will be useless.

249
00:17:17,333 --> 00:17:19,633
Yenyen will come back alive.

250
00:17:20,800 --> 00:17:22,767
I believe that she'll come back.

251
00:17:25,167 --> 00:17:26,233
Who can blame her?

252
00:17:27,233 --> 00:17:28,800
What you did was wrong.

253
00:17:31,133 --> 00:17:33,633
You're lucky she
doesn't have money.

254
00:17:34,100 --> 00:17:38,367
Because if she's someone
who has money to sue,

255
00:17:38,433 --> 00:17:39,733
what will happen to us?

256
00:17:41,100 --> 00:17:42,367
What will happen
to my reputation?

257
00:17:43,000 --> 00:17:46,233
Rina, we cannot afford
to lose investors

258
00:17:46,300 --> 00:17:48,333
in our rural banks in Quezon.

259
00:17:48,433 --> 00:17:50,667
So please, next time,

260
00:17:50,733 --> 00:17:54,733
think before you make some mess.

261
00:17:55,433 --> 00:17:56,233
Don't worry.

262
00:17:58,000 --> 00:18:02,400
I won't make a mess again...

263
00:18:03,933 --> 00:18:06,933
once I clean up every trash.

264
00:18:39,367 --> 00:18:42,133
Your boyfriend is so lucky.

265
00:18:43,400 --> 00:18:44,367
He's been so lucky, right?

266
00:18:44,433 --> 00:18:45,500
You talk too much.

267
00:18:45,567 --> 00:18:47,100
Can't we just be happy

268
00:18:47,167 --> 00:18:48,433
because we have something
to eat later?

269
00:18:48,500 --> 00:18:49,200
Okay.

270
00:18:50,733 --> 00:18:51,100
Ow!
Oh my God!

271
00:18:52,100 --> 00:18:53,500
Ouch!

272
00:18:53,567 --> 00:18:54,067
My leg!
My leg!

273
00:18:54,733 --> 00:18:56,000
Red, help me, please!

274
00:18:57,167 --> 00:18:58,067
My leg!
Please!

275
00:18:59,100 --> 00:18:59,900
Sab!

276
00:18:59,967 --> 00:19:01,033
It really hurts.
Please, help me.

277
00:19:01,100 --> 00:19:02,633
- Please!
- Sab, what happened?

278
00:19:03,967 --> 00:19:04,900
I don't know.

279
00:19:04,967 --> 00:19:07,133
I think I stepped
on a sea creature.

280
00:19:07,200 --> 00:19:08,400
Please, help me. Please.

281
00:19:08,467 --> 00:19:08,933
Ouch!

282
00:19:14,600 --> 00:19:15,067
Help!

283
00:19:15,567 --> 00:19:16,133
Help, please!

284
00:19:17,067 --> 00:19:18,867
I can't move my leg.
Please, please.

285
00:19:20,633 --> 00:19:21,467
Please, help.

286
00:19:22,400 --> 00:19:23,167
It's painful.

287
00:19:31,833 --> 00:19:32,467
Thank you.

288
00:19:33,267 --> 00:19:34,633
Sorry, sorry.

289
00:19:35,233 --> 00:19:37,300
I think I stepped
on a sea creature.

290
00:19:37,833 --> 00:19:38,800
Sorry.

291
00:19:57,733 --> 00:19:58,933
I'm sorry.

292
00:20:01,567 --> 00:20:02,133
Over there.

293
00:20:02,600 --> 00:20:03,567
You can now put me down there.

294
00:20:08,167 --> 00:20:09,200
Thank you.

295
00:20:13,100 --> 00:20:14,067
- What happened?
- Can you help me?

296
00:20:14,133 --> 00:20:15,700
My leg hurts.

297
00:20:15,767 --> 00:20:17,067
Please, I can't move it.

298
00:20:17,500 --> 00:20:19,433
- Here?
- Yeah, yeah, there.

299
00:20:19,500 --> 00:20:20,133
Yeah.

300
00:20:20,200 --> 00:20:21,333
Yeah, just keep doing that.

301
00:20:25,067 --> 00:20:27,200
Are you okay, Sabina?

302
00:20:27,267 --> 00:20:28,100
Yeah, I'm okay.

303
00:20:28,167 --> 00:20:29,300
Red is here.

304
00:20:29,367 --> 00:20:31,400
He knows what he's doing.

305
00:20:31,467 --> 00:20:32,133
Thank you.

306
00:20:33,767 --> 00:20:36,367
Okay, just let us know
if you need anything.

307
00:20:36,967 --> 00:20:38,533
We'll just find some firewood.

308
00:20:39,033 --> 00:20:40,533
- Okay.
- Let's go, Raichu.

309
00:20:41,700 --> 00:20:42,400
- Thanks.
- Here, Eden.

310
00:20:42,700 --> 00:20:43,467
Thank you.

311
00:20:44,467 --> 00:20:47,133
- Let's split so we'll be fast.
- Firewood?

312
00:20:47,200 --> 00:20:48,733
We can use that.

313
00:20:49,367 --> 00:20:50,600
Thank you.

314
00:20:53,733 --> 00:20:55,567
Oh, wait. Where are you going?
Don't leave me.

315
00:20:56,333 --> 00:20:58,833
I haven't thanked
you properly yet.

316
00:21:00,033 --> 00:21:00,867
Thank you.

317
00:21:01,467 --> 00:21:02,367
What are you doing?

318
00:21:03,333 --> 00:21:04,267
There's no one else here.

319
00:21:04,333 --> 00:21:05,400
So maybe we can...

320
00:21:06,933 --> 00:21:07,400
Sab.

321
00:21:08,100 --> 00:21:08,700
No.

322
00:21:09,100 --> 00:21:10,967
But I miss you.
What's your problem?

323
00:21:11,500 --> 00:21:14,733
I thought we were going to find
a way to fix our relationship.

324
00:21:15,100 --> 00:21:16,467
I thought we were okay.

325
00:21:18,000 --> 00:21:19,400
We're okay.

326
00:21:19,933 --> 00:21:21,933
But that doesn't mean
we'll get back together.

327
00:21:22,800 --> 00:21:25,000
Why? Is it because of Yenyen?

328
00:21:25,767 --> 00:21:27,333
I saw the way you
looked at her earlier.

329
00:21:27,967 --> 00:21:29,200
You never looked at me
like that.

330
00:21:30,133 --> 00:21:33,467
So? What? Are you going to
tell me you like her more?

331
00:21:33,533 --> 00:21:35,233
What if I say yes?

332
00:21:36,133 --> 00:21:36,833
No way!

333
00:21:38,133 --> 00:21:39,100
You're mine, Red.

334
00:21:39,167 --> 00:21:40,133
Please, you're mine.

335
00:21:41,133 --> 00:21:41,700
No way.

336
00:21:42,233 --> 00:21:44,567
If I have to keep talking
to Yenyen

337
00:21:44,633 --> 00:21:46,700
to make her leave us alone,
I'll do it!

338
00:21:46,767 --> 00:21:48,167
Because I want you
to be mine again!

339
00:21:48,867 --> 00:21:49,333
This is so annoying!

340
00:21:51,100 --> 00:21:51,733
Sab!

341
00:21:53,100 --> 00:21:54,433
Sab, come back here!

342
00:21:56,200 --> 00:21:58,100
I'm sorry, Dindi.

343
00:21:58,167 --> 00:22:00,233
I won't ask you to come
with me next time.

344
00:22:00,300 --> 00:22:03,233
You skipped work for nothing.

345
00:22:04,433 --> 00:22:07,767
I've been giving you
nothing but trouble.

346
00:22:08,567 --> 00:22:10,400
Come on! It's nothing.
I promise.

347
00:22:10,467 --> 00:22:12,667
As they say, don't mention it.

348
00:22:12,733 --> 00:22:14,900
I can just make an excuse.
I promise.

349
00:22:15,000 --> 00:22:17,500
To convince you,
remember my suitors...

350
00:22:17,567 --> 00:22:19,533
back when I still
had many suitors...

351
00:22:19,600 --> 00:22:22,767
I can avoid them no
matter how bad they look.

352
00:22:22,833 --> 00:22:24,500
This is easier than that.

353
00:22:24,567 --> 00:22:27,967
We got each other's back.

354
00:22:28,667 --> 00:22:29,767
Thank you.

355
00:22:29,833 --> 00:22:31,400
Are you Amanda Sta. Maria?

356
00:22:33,567 --> 00:22:34,133
Yes, why?

357
00:22:34,667 --> 00:22:36,467
Is it true that you
just got out of jail?

358
00:22:36,533 --> 00:22:38,533
We heard that you were involved
in murdering a child.

359
00:22:38,600 --> 00:22:41,067
- That's right!
- She's a murderer.

360
00:22:41,133 --> 00:22:42,300
You can't stay in our
neighborhood

361
00:22:42,367 --> 00:22:43,533
if you really are a criminal.

362
00:22:43,600 --> 00:22:45,333
We won't feel safe as
long as you're here.

363
00:22:45,400 --> 00:22:47,333
- Yes, that's right!
- I agree.

364
00:22:47,400 --> 00:22:48,267
That's dangerous.

365
00:22:49,033 --> 00:22:49,700
Yenyen!

366
00:22:50,400 --> 00:22:51,133
Yenyen!

367
00:22:51,900 --> 00:22:52,533
Sabina.

368
00:22:53,600 --> 00:22:54,300
What are you doing here?

369
00:22:54,367 --> 00:22:55,500
Is your wound okay now?

370
00:22:55,933 --> 00:22:57,933
I thought you would
stay away from Red.

371
00:22:58,733 --> 00:23:00,967
But it seems that you're
making him more confused.

372
00:23:01,033 --> 00:23:02,800
Actually, it's not just that.

373
00:23:02,867 --> 00:23:04,500
You're ruining our relationship!

374
00:23:05,167 --> 00:23:07,833
Sabina, I have no intention of
ruining your relationship.

375
00:23:09,700 --> 00:23:11,433
If I only knew he was in
a relationship with you,

376
00:23:11,500 --> 00:23:12,667
I would have avoided him.

377
00:23:12,733 --> 00:23:13,633
Really?

378
00:23:13,700 --> 00:23:15,767
I don't care about
your explanation.

379
00:23:15,833 --> 00:23:17,533
Just stay away from him!

380
00:23:18,033 --> 00:23:20,867
What else do you want me
to do, Sabina?

381
00:23:20,933 --> 00:23:21,733
Oh my gosh!

382
00:23:24,100 --> 00:23:24,533
Oh my God!

383
00:23:26,133 --> 00:23:27,167
What is happening?
Help me!

384
00:23:28,733 --> 00:23:29,367
Help me!

385
00:23:32,100 --> 00:23:32,433
Help!

386
00:23:32,967 --> 00:23:33,700
Help!

387
00:23:33,767 --> 00:23:35,433
- Help!
- Help us!

388
00:23:35,500 --> 00:23:36,333
Help us, please!
Please, help!

389
00:23:37,767 --> 00:23:38,433
Help us!

390
00:23:38,500 --> 00:23:40,567
Raichu, help!

391
00:23:41,333 --> 00:23:42,267
Who told you that?

392
00:23:42,767 --> 00:23:43,267
She went to jail.

393
00:23:43,967 --> 00:23:45,100
- She went to jail.
- And even killed someone.

394
00:23:45,167 --> 00:23:46,600
Can I...

395
00:23:46,667 --> 00:23:48,033
it's not what you think.

396
00:23:48,100 --> 00:23:49,500
Can you please hear me out?

397
00:23:49,567 --> 00:23:51,233
You don't need to explain.

398
00:23:51,300 --> 00:23:53,067
You shouldn't be here.

399
00:23:53,133 --> 00:23:54,633
- Leave!
- Yes!

400
00:23:54,700 --> 00:23:55,533
- She's right!
- Get out of here!

401
00:23:55,633 --> 00:23:57,433
We won't let a
criminal live here.

402
00:23:57,500 --> 00:23:58,667
We don't want to take a risk.

403
00:23:59,600 --> 00:24:01,500
What if you hurt our children?

404
00:24:02,267 --> 00:24:03,133
- That's right!
- That's right!

405
00:24:04,000 --> 00:24:05,767
- We're not safe with you here!
- You should leave.

406
00:24:05,833 --> 00:24:07,867
- Do you think we're fools?
- We won't allow a criminal

407
00:24:07,933 --> 00:24:08,800
to live in our neighborhood!

408
00:24:08,867 --> 00:24:10,167
- Just leave!
- I'm not a criminal.

409
00:24:10,233 --> 00:24:11,467
I'm not a criminal!

410
00:24:11,533 --> 00:24:12,733
Oh, come on!

411
00:24:12,800 --> 00:24:14,600
- We won't believe you.
- I didn't kill anybody!

412
00:24:14,667 --> 00:24:15,533
Yes, I went to jail.

413
00:24:15,600 --> 00:24:16,867
But I was just accused.

414
00:24:16,933 --> 00:24:17,733
I didn't have anything to do

415
00:24:17,800 --> 00:24:19,067
with what happened
to that child!

416
00:24:19,133 --> 00:24:21,067
Hold on. How dare you
raise your voices!

417
00:24:21,133 --> 00:24:22,833
The nerve of you to judge!

418
00:24:22,900 --> 00:24:24,367
Who do you think you are?

419
00:24:25,367 --> 00:24:29,233
Are you some judge to
be that judgmental?

420
00:24:29,333 --> 00:24:31,900
- Hey!
- You don't have the right

421
00:24:31,967 --> 00:24:32,833
to judge my sister!

422
00:24:32,900 --> 00:24:34,767
You don't know what
really happened!

423
00:24:34,833 --> 00:24:36,333
We know it. Someone told us!

424
00:24:36,400 --> 00:24:37,933
- Yes, that's right!
- That's right!

425
00:24:38,000 --> 00:24:39,633
Who told you?
Who was it?

426
00:24:39,700 --> 00:24:40,667
- Who told you?
- You don't need to know!

427
00:24:41,133 --> 00:24:42,500
- You don't need to know!
- Who told you?

428
00:24:42,567 --> 00:24:44,400
- We want you out of here!
- Leave, or we will report you

429
00:24:44,467 --> 00:24:44,933
to the barangay!

430
00:24:45,000 --> 00:24:46,900
Hey! Hold on! FYI!

431
00:24:46,967 --> 00:24:48,333
FYI for the second time.

432
00:24:48,400 --> 00:24:50,000
For you, narrow-minded

433
00:24:50,067 --> 00:24:52,333
- gossipers and meddlers!
- Whatever!

434
00:24:52,400 --> 00:24:54,800
What you're doing is illegal!

435
00:24:54,867 --> 00:24:57,600
You can kick people
out at your whim!

436
00:24:57,667 --> 00:25:00,467
Or just because she
went to jail!

437
00:25:00,533 --> 00:25:02,500
Fine! Let's say she
went to jail.

438
00:25:02,600 --> 00:25:04,667
Can't she have a
second chance at life?

439
00:25:04,733 --> 00:25:06,367
- Second chance?
- The operation cleanup

440
00:25:06,433 --> 00:25:10,033
has already started for Amanda.

441
00:25:11,833 --> 00:25:14,933
Trash like her should
be disregarded...

442
00:25:17,267 --> 00:25:18,333
should be thrown out...

443
00:25:19,767 --> 00:25:22,267
and shouldn't be recycled...

444
00:25:23,900 --> 00:25:24,667
ever.

445
00:25:31,100 --> 00:25:34,867
Let's see where you'll
end up, Amanda.

446
00:25:36,033 --> 00:25:36,533
Help!

447
00:25:37,567 --> 00:25:38,400
Raichu!

448
00:25:40,500 --> 00:25:42,233
Red, help!

449
00:25:42,300 --> 00:25:43,200
Oh my God, Red!

450
00:25:43,767 --> 00:25:44,800
Oh my God, help us!

451
00:25:44,867 --> 00:25:46,467
- Please, help me!
- Yen, Sab!

452
00:25:47,733 --> 00:25:48,533
Amanda!

453
00:25:48,600 --> 00:25:49,933
We know everything
about you!

454
00:25:50,000 --> 00:25:52,600
We're going to the village chief
to file a complaint against you!

455
00:25:52,667 --> 00:25:54,800
You should leave if you don't
want to get embarrassed!

456
00:25:55,633 --> 00:25:57,633
Leave, you criminals!

457
00:25:57,700 --> 00:26:00,433
- Leave!
- Get out of here!

458
00:26:00,500 --> 00:26:06,600
- Get out of there!
- Leave!

459
00:26:06,833 --> 00:26:08,033
How long will you avoid me?

460
00:26:08,500 --> 00:26:09,833
Because I can't do it anymore.

461
00:26:11,000 --> 00:26:12,367
But it's you I really like.

462
00:26:12,967 --> 00:26:13,833
I miss you.

463
00:26:16,600 --> 00:26:17,833
I really miss you.
